name: integer_i64_sign_extended_i32_minimum
description: |
  This is i32 minimum represented as i64, requiring the upper
  32 bits to be set during sign extension. It catches zero-extension,
  partial-register, and widening-conversion bugs while preserving the value
  -2147483648.
format: hex
decode-as: i64
pair:
  - with: ../i32/minimum.input
    hint: equal
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "signed-integer"
  - "i64"
  - "sign-extension"
  - "conversion"
  - "lower-width"
  - "two's-complement"
---
00 00 00 80 ff ff ff ff   # -2147483648
